    {
        "content": "<p>Very nice!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://florisvandoorn.com/carleson/docs/find/?pattern=CompatibleFunctions.le_cdist#doc\">carleson#CompatibleFunctions.le_cdist</a> shows that if <code>dist_{x₁, r} θ (Q x) &gt; 0</code> then <code>upperRadius Q θ x &lt; ∞</code>. If <code>dist_{x₁, r} θ (Q x) = 0</code>, then <code>upperRadius</code> will indeed be infinity... I'm not quite sure what to do in that case, let me ask Lars.</p>",
